Enlarge this image toggle caption Justin Edmonds/Getty Images Justin Edmonds/Getty ImagesVon Miller, the defensive star for the Denver Broncos, announced he has tested positive for the coronavirus.
Miller is a former Super Bowl MVP and was the second overall pick in the 2011 NFL Draft.
"After experiencing flu-like symptoms, Denver Broncos linebacker Von Miller has tested positive for COVID-19.
Von has elected to share his diagnosis publicly to emphasize that anyone can be afflicted with coronavirus," the Broncos' statement said.
Earlier this week, Los Angeles Rams center Brian Allen said he has tested positive for the coronavirus.